710482f-b.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 18th Street (West)
710482f-b.text:
Tenth Avenue, west side, north from W. 18th Street
(extreme left and not seen ), showing structures occupying
the 19th-20th Street frontage. At the left is a vacant lot
on the eaaterly half of the 18th-19th Street block and across
which appears buildings on the north aide of W. 19th Street.
The gap shown there was caused by the demolition in 19E0
of a 3 story tenement, No. 5O7-9 W. 19th Street. View No. 2
is a closer view of this N.W. corner of the Avenue and W. 19th
Street and :hows in addition the renovation of the adjoininm
atructure to the aforerentioned gap.
July 28, 1931
View 2: July 18, 19S2.
P.L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
